cff-version: 1.2.0

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CITATION.cff
# CRM Customer Intelligence Module
#
# Cite this repository if you use the architecture patterns, SQL ETL
# procedures, ML pipeline design, survival-analysis approach, Power BI
# themes, or any other artefacts from this project in your own work.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

message: >
  If you use any part of this project — the medallion lakehouse schema,
  ML pipeline design, Weibull AFT next-purchase model, Portuguese sentiment
  integration, Power BI themes, or CRM action queue pattern — please cite
  it using the metadata below.

title: "CRM Customer Intelligence Module"

abstract: >
  A production-grade CRM intelligence system built on a medallion lakehouse
  (Bronze → Silver → Gold) in SQL Server, with a Python ML pipeline running
  five models (Portuguese sentiment analysis via LeIA, RFM rule-based
  segmentation + K-means clustering, XGBoost CLV with quantile confidence
  intervals, XGBoost churn classification with F1-tuned threshold, and
  Weibull AFT survival analysis for next-purchase timing), a JSON-driven
  CRM action queue rule engine, and seven Power BI dashboards. Applied to
  the Olist Brazilian E-Commerce Public Dataset (96,096 unified customers,
  R$15.84M GMV). Includes two complete custom Power BI JSON theme files
  (Warm Clay and Ember) submitted to the Microsoft Fabric Community Themes
  Gallery.

